  <dashboards>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard'>
      <style />
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='86870' id='25' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98462' x='769' y='11976'>
            <zone h='86870' id='20' type-v2='layout-basic' w='98462' x='769' y='11976'>
              <zone h='86870' id='8' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='86246' x='769' y='11976'>
                <zone h='86870' id='6' type-v2='layout-basic' w='48458' x='769' y='11976'>
                  <zone h='43435' id='3' name='chart 5' w='34326' x='769' y='55411'>
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                  <zone forceUpdate='true' h='43435' id='10' type-v2='text' w='14132' x='35095' y='55411'>
                    <formatted-text>
                      <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The gap between Malaysia and Indonesia widens when overtime regulations are considered. While standard working hours differ by only 5 hours per week, the maximum legally permitted workload differs by 13 hours (Malaysian employees can legally work up to 71 hours per week (45 + 26), compared to 58 hours per week in Indonesia (40 + 18)), suggesting that overtime policies have a greater impact on labour intensity than standard workweek regulations.</run>
                    </formatted-text>
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                  <zone forceUpdate='true' h='43435' id='11' type-v2='text' w='14131' x='35096' y='11976'>
                    <formatted-text>
                      <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Prior to 2024, Indonesia consistently offered stronger maternity protection with 90 days of leave compared to Malaysia&apos;s 60 days. However, Malaysia&apos;s landmark reform in 2024 extended maternity leave to 98 days, surpassing Indonesia for the first time and signaling a major shift toward more progressive family-friendly labor policies.</run>
                    </formatted-text>
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                  <zone h='43435' id='15' name='chart 2' w='34327' x='769' y='11976'>
                    <layout-cache minheight='246' minwidth='159' type-h='scalable' type-w='scalable' />
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='393' h='86870' id='7' is-fixed='true' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='37788' x='49227' y='11976'>
                  <zone h='34921' id='14' name='chart 1' w='37788' x='49227' y='11976'>
                    <layout-cache minheight='242' minwidth='152' type-h='scalable' type-w='scalable' />
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                  <zone h='51949' id='23' name='chart 4' w='37788' x='49227' y='46897'>
                    <layout-cache cell-count-w='2' minheight='429' non-cell-size-w='60' type-h='scalable' type-w='cell' />
                    <zone-style>
                      <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                      <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                      <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                      <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    </zone-style>
                  </zone>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='43437' id='17' type-v2='text' w='12216' x='87015' y='55409'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Indonesia offers more generous time-off provisions, particularly in public holidays and weekly rest entitlements. While leave compensation remains comparable between the two countries, the differences in rest-related benefits highlight distinct approaches to employee welfare and work-life balance</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Helvetica Neue'>.</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone h='43433' id='28' type-v2='text' w='12216' x='87015' y='11976'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Malaysia implemented reforms that reduced the legal workweek, while Indonesia&apos;s limit remained largely unchanged throughout the period. This demonstrates how labour regulations evolve differently across countries and highlights varying approaches to worker protection.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone h='10822' id='27' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98462' x='769' y='1154'>
            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='10822' id='18' type-v2='text' w='98462' x='769' y='1154'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Impact' fontsize='20'>Reform in Motion: How Malaysia and Indonesia&apos;s Labour Laws Have Evolved</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
