                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Indonesia offers more generous time-off provisions, particularly in public holidays and weekly rest entitlements. While leave compensation remains comparable between the two countries, the differences in rest-related benefits highlight distinct approaches to employee welfare and work-life balance</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Helvetica Neue'>.</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='280' h='43435' id='3' is-fixed='true' name='chart 5' w='34326' x='769' y='55411'>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='43435' id='10' type-v2='text' w='14132' x='35095' y='55411'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The gap between Malaysia and Indonesia widens when overtime regulations are considered. While standard working hours differ by only 5 hours per week, the maximum legally permitted workload differs by 13 hours (Malaysian employees can legally work up to 71 hours per week (45 + 26), compared to 58 hours per week in Indonesia (40 + 18)), suggesting that overtime policies have a greater impact on labour intensity than standard workweek regulations.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
